elements.title: Albert helmet
elements.contents: ... that a version of the Albert helmet proposed by Prince Albert in 1842 is still worn by the British Army's Household Cavalry (soldiers pictured)?

elements.title: Yasunori Oshima
elements.contents: ... that Yasunori Oshima served as the hitting coach for the Japan national baseball team that won the inaugural World Baseball Classic in 2006?

elements.title: Chi Mat Ba Ram
elements.contents: ... that although "Chi Mat Ba Ram", the title of the song by Brave Girls, translates to "the swish of a skirt" in Korean, a term that is often used negatively, the song is about the fierceness in women?

elements.title: Pedro X. Molina
elements.contents: ... that Nicaraguan cartoonist Pedro X. Molina has had to flee his home country twice in his lifetime?

elements.title: Police Anti-Terrorist Unit
elements.contents: ... that the Police Anti-Terrorist Unit joined Rhodesian military operations in police uniform and were only issued camouflage after a soldier hesitated because a target wore the same colour trousers?

elements.title: Alvin Bragg
elements.contents: ... that Alvin Bragg has overseen lawsuits against the Donald J. Trump Foundation, Harvey Weinstein, and The Weinstein Company, and represented the families of Eric Garner and Ramarley Graham?

elements.title: lap steel guitar
elements.contents: ... that the lap steel guitar was the first "foreign" musical instrument to gain a foothold in American pop music?

elements.title: Queen Alice
elements.contents: ... that during the War of the Lombards, fighting was interrupted so that the corpse of the besieged Queen Alice could be handed over to her husband, who had never seen her alive?
